            <bug_when>2007-08-07 00:31:54 +0200</bug_when>
            <thetext>It seems that the TreeFile/Folder does not adapt the width of it&#39;s row structure.
This causes ui cheese when you have horizontal scrollbars and a backgroundcolor because the backgroundcolor is only drawed for the size of the Tree itself and not for the rest of the scrollable area.

Workaround: Setting the width of the TreeItem to the full size of the row works. But i think this should be handled by qooxdoo.

See attached snippet which reproduces the problem</thetext>
